Package: slimrlang
Title: Write SLiM Population Genetics Simulation Scripts in R
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Russell",
           family = "Dinnage",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "russell.dinnage@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0846-2819"))
Description: An R package that lets you write SLiM scripts using your favourite R IDE, using a syntax as cose as possible to the original SLiM language. This pacakge mostly exists to complement slimr, which has much more functionality for running SLiM from R and which imports this package.
